comment._content:
Marson Lockheed Twins has it as Lockheed Lodestar 18-56-23/C-60A-5-LO 42-56083 USAAF 5 October 1943. To NC13K 31 January 1946, then N13K, N1929, N1846, N1846G. was 5-stretcher ambulance plane for Schaefer ca. 1962.
Believed derelict in Peru, possibly now preserved Las Palmas AB Peru as FAP-512.
Non-standard radar nose in pic.
